The method takes:
- the string to parse
- the pattern to describe the portion to be parsed
- the pattern to split that portion
    
It works as follows:
- first the method streams the matches
- then it splits them
- converts to an int
- and returns them in an array.
```    
public static int[] getValues(String line, String pattern,
        String splitPat) {
    return Pattern.compile(pattern).matcher(line).results()
            .flatMap(mr -&gt; Arrays.stream(mr.group().split(splitPat)))
            .mapToInt(Integer::parseInt).toArray();
}
```
